# ArticleCardBySlug

**File:** `app/components/ArticleCardBySlug.tsx`

## Purpose

Looks up an article by slug from the article registry, resolves its author, formats its publication date, applies a fallback image, and renders the project `ArticleCard`. Article navigation must use React Router paths.

## Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---:|---|
| `slug` | `string` | — | Article slug to look up in the registry. |
| `ctaText` | `string` | `"Read more"` | Call-to-action text passed to `ArticleCard`. |
| `className` | `string` | — | Additional classes passed to `ArticleCard`. |
| `descriptionOverride` | `string` | — | Replaces the registry description. |
| `variant` | `"default" \| "compact"` | `"default"` | Card size variant. |
| `authorOverride` | `Author` | — | Replaces the author resolved from the authors registry. |

## Semantic Hints

`card`, `article-card`, `slug-card`, `dynamic-card`, `registry-card`, `auto-card`

## Behavior

1. Finds the matching article in `articles` using `slug`.
2. Returns `null` and logs a warning when no article exists.
3. Resolves the author from `authors` unless `authorOverride` is provided.
4. Uses a fallback image when the article has no image.
5. Passes `/articles/${slug}` to `ArticleCard`; `ArticleCard` should render this destination with React Router’s `Link`.
6. Adds no wrapper styling beyond `className` forwarded to `ArticleCard`.

